Package fr.enseeiht.danck.voice_analyzer

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Connector
    A tool for binding some user database with the VoiceAnalyzer.
    MetaTokenListener
    An item to be signaled to inform which MetaToken has been detected.
    Parser
    A parser able to parse series of (Meta)Token and generating (Meta)Orders.
    VoiceListener
    An item to be signaled to inform whether or not some voice has been detected.
    WindowMaker
    A tool responsible for cutting the signal into several small windows.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Cleaner
    A tool responsible for computing the noise definition from MFCC samples and removing it from other MFCCs.
    DTWHelper
    A tool for computing DTW on Fields.
    Extractor
    A tool responsible for extracting suitable MFCC from the inputted signal.
    Field
    A cluster of MFCC representing a piece of signal corresponding to either a contiguous segment of speech or a amount of silence.
    Finder
    A tool responsible for finding from database the best MetaToken compared to a given one (or nothing).
    MetaOrder
    The class representing a MetaOrder, which is composed of an Order and associated Data
    MetaToken
    The class representing a MetaOrder, which is composed of a Token and associated Data
    MFCC
    A structure representing information about a piece of signal (Mel-frequency cepstrum).
    MFCCHelper
    A tool for manipulating MFCCs.
    Order
    A Pseudo-Enumeration representing the Orders generated by the Parser.
    Sorter
    A tool responsible for distinguish Voice from Silence among series of MFCCs.
    Token
    A Pseudo-Enumeration representing the Tokens used by the Parser.
    VoiceAnalyzer
    The main class responsible for coordinating all classes related to the signal process and analyze.
    VoiceAnalyzerMulti
    A 'MutliThread' version of the VoiceAnalyzer.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    NoiseUndefinedException
    A classic Exception used when trying to get noise from the cleaner while it wasn't fed enough.
    UnknownOrderException
    A classic Exception used when nothing can be understood by the parser.
    VoiceAnalyzerRecordException
    A classic Exception used when something bad happened during recording.
